&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sandfox is building an adaptive buyer-led discovery platform for enterprise B2B.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is a world where every business interaction adapts to buyer context, where companies understand what buyers are trying to accomplish and deliver the information, guidance, and experiences they need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, most B2B buying experiences are static. Websites, content hubs, and campaigns deliver the same experience regardless of who the buyer is or what they need. Sandfox transforms fragmented buyer data into structured intelligence that powers adaptive experiences, helping companies deliver relevance instead of noise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sandfox is a portfolio company of super{set}, a venture studio that conceives, funds, and builds AI-native companies from formation through scale. We work alongside founders as operators, helping shape companies from day one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re a small, early-stage team building something that doesn&#39;t exist yet in the market. The work is hands-on, the problems are difficult, and the opportunity to shape both product and company from the ground up is significant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for our first engineering hire: a Founding Engineer who will shape both the product and the technical foundation of Sandfox.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll work directly with the founder to turn product vision into production software, establish engineering standards, and define how adaptive buyer experiences should work in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role goes beyond engineering execution. We&#39;re building a new category of software where user experience, information architecture, AI orchestration, and interface design are deeply intertwined. You&#39;ll help shape not only how the platform works, but how it feels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone energized by ownership, ambiguity, and the opportunity to build elegant solutions to complex problems from the ground up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHY THIS ROLE MATTERS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The technical challenge is only part of what we&#39;re solving. Sandfox sits at the intersection of AI, buyer psychology, workflow design, and user experience. The winners in this category won&#39;t simply have the best models or infrastructure. They&#39;ll create experiences that feel intuitive, adaptive, and genuinely useful. As Sandfox&#39;s first engineering hire, you&#39;ll help define what the next generation of B2B buying experiences looks like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL OWN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll own the technical foundation of Sandfox, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-powered workflows and user experiences that transform buyer context into adaptive discovery journeys and seller intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product quality and design craftsmanship across the customer experience, from first interaction through ongoing usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Production systems that combine retrieval, reasoning, evaluation, and user feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scalable backend services and data pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer-facing applications used by enterprise teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal tooling, infrastructure, and deployment systems that support rapid iteration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
